Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb}. Trim and finely chop @scallions{2}. Quarter @lime{1}. Trim and halve @Brussels sprouts{8%ounce}.

Toss Brussels sprouts on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{} and a big pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack for ~{12%minutes}, then remove from oven and carefully toss with @soy sauce{2%teaspoon} (4 tsp for 4 servings; save the rest for step 6). Return Brussels sprouts to oven until browned and crispy, ~{3-5%minutes} more.

Meanwhile, melt @butter{1%tablespoon} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add 1 TBSP minced ginger (2 TBSP for 4 servings). Cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds} to ~{1%minute}. Add @water{3/4%cup} (1 1/2 cups for 4) and a pinch of @salt{}, then bring to a boil. Stir in @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, in a #medium bowl{}, combine scallions, @sesame oil{1%tablespoon}, 1 tsp minced ginger (2 tsp for 4 servings), 1 tsp @sugar{1%teaspoon} (2 tsp for 4), juice from half the lime, and @sriracha{1%teaspoon} to taste. Season with salt and pepper. Taste and add more ginger or lime juice if you feel like something's missing.

Pat @Australis barramundi{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with salt and pepper. Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{4%teaspoon} in a large, preferably nonstick, pan over medium-high heat. Add barramundi to pan, skin sides down; cook until lightly browned and crispy, ~{3-4%minutes}. Carefully flip and cook until fish is firm and cooked through, ~{3-4%minutes} more.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) until melted. Season with salt and pepper. Divide rice and Brussels sprouts between plates. Top with barramundi and pesto. Drizzle with remaining soy sauce to taste. Serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.